RACE.FOOTNOTES: MONTICELLO took over from between rivals early then dropped in to set a rated pace, handled some outside pressure while rated along through the backstretch run, dug in when confronted by TALES TO TELL entering the lane, was dogged by that one past the furlong grounds, shook clear under strong handling with a sixteenth to go and held firm. TALES TO TELL , well placed saving ground while in range, edged closer leaving the far turn, eased out and bid between foes into the lane, battled outside the winner past mid stretch, wandered outward, corrected but was kept at bay. VICTORY BADGE , taken to rate while saving ground, came under a ride mid way on the final turn, slipped thru to the inside a trio of runners entering the stretch and churned on. SHARMIN drifted out nearing the first turn, was straightened and prompted three wide outside the winner, drifted out a bit nearing the lane and faded through the final three sixteenths. FIRST TO ARRIVE , a bit sluggish from the gate, drafted in towards the rail early on and settled, angled out and was called upon between foes past the five sixteenths, raced three wide into the lane but came up empty. SHOCKING FACTS , floated out four wide by SHARMIN into the first turn, corrected and moved up outside a rival to stalk, failed to go on nearing the lane and retreated. TWIRL THE FLAG , three to four wide, failed to respond. PACIFIC FRONT lagged back while saving ground, dropped far off the pace around the final turn then was eased through the final furlong.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: AMERICAN UNITY settled in range while off the inside, angled out and was put to a hustling ride leaving the eighths, advanced four wide into the stretch, closed in under stout asking and engaged the leader nearing the furlong marker, dueled while being floated out, wrested command with about a sixteenth to go and drew away late. GUNSLINGER (IRE) cleared early and set the pace towards the rail while under a light hold, came under coaxing past the five sixteenths, dug in when confronted nearing the eighth pole, wandered outward several paths while battling past the sixteenth marker, gave way grudgingly and held down the place. SIR TERRE steadied off heels when a bit keen and saving ground under the wire the first time, settled through the backstretch run, angled five wide approaching the stretch, moved up nearing mid stretch, shifted back in and kept on willingly to the inside of GUNSLINGER (IRE). JOHNG , unhurried early while saving ground, edged up past the three eighths, worked outward to about the five path entering the lane, switched over to his left lead when advancing inside the furlong grounds then churned on to the wire. BONDED saved ground stalking the pace, was lightly steadied near the far turn, remained inside making progress past mid stretch then flattened out. POWER BACK was steadied briefly near the seven eighths, steadied along between runners mid way on the first turn, came five to six wide for the drive and had belated action. IMAGINE IT ALL , three wide early, stalked off the inside, gave hard chase into the stretch and faded. FERMAT saved ground off the pace, made a mild run nearing the lane then lacked any further kick. BATTALION broke a step slow, stalked three wide, failed to keep pace nearing the lane and retreated. NEVERFOLD , off the rail, faltered leaving the far turn.

LADY BANKER prompted the pace outside the winner, moved to apply more pressure exiting the far turn, dueled to upper stretch, stayed on to about the sixteenth marker then faded late. LENAMAGNETTA broke slowly, rated to the inside of foes mid turn, angled four to five wide for the drive and finished with interest. TEA ROSE saved ground mid turn, edged up to the inside of runners leaving mid stretch, eased out late and finished with good energy. LENDHERCREDIT gave early chase two wide, raced three wide into the stretch but lacked a rally. GOLDEN CHARM , soundly bumped at the break, raced off the pace and between rivals mid turn, came four wide for the drive but lacked a rally. CATCH THE KITTEN , three deep early, raced five wide into the lane but failed to menace.
